> Here is exactly what screenshots to take and where to save them:

| Filename | What to capture |
|---|---|
| `screenshots/dashboard_overview.png` | Full first page of the dashboard (Executive Overview) |
| `screenshots/category_breakdown.png` | The category/brand analysis page |
| `screenshots/customer_insights.png` | Customer behaviour or ratings page |
| `screenshots/sales_trends.png` | Time-series or trends page |
| `screenshots/excel_pivot.png` *(optional)* | A key pivot table or chart from the Excel workbook |
| `screenshots/data_model.png` *(optional)* | The Power BI Model view showing table relationships |

**How to take a clean screenshot in Power BI:**
1. Set the report view to **Fit to Page** (View â†’ Fit to Page)
2. Press `Windows + Shift + S` to snip the dashboard area
3. Save at full resolution (1920Ã—1080 or higher recommended)

